abstract.p:
                  Reliability evaluation is an important task in safety–critical applications. The failure of a system is generally caused by random shocks resulting from adverse events or internal degradations. This chapter thus mainly focuses on the review of system reliability models with random shocks and the uncertainty of the degradation process. In the category of system reliability models with random shocks, we review system reliability models based on five random shock models that are commonly used in Reliability Engineering, cumulative shock model, extreme shock model, run shock model, 



